The paper discusses the issue of information relevance in knowledge bases, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research. The approach used by the Catsear team involves combining answers from different sources using a linear regression classifier, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of a classifier also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
